Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_4051
Response Text: I go back to getting more funding. I just don’t see how you can improve without the ability to expand support/funding options to all artists, organizations, and communities. Because if you think about it artists (I include visual, musical, and theater performers) are a historically under-funded segment of society. The lucky few find their patron, have the financial infrastructure already in place so they can get help at home or in their studio. The rest of us are scrambling. And from what I know of other cities in this country that provide more funding to support their local artists, the cultural infrastructure becomes inherently more inclusive. It also helps to expand the commercial potential. Consider the way the city hypes Austin as the Music Capitol of the World. How many music venues exist in Austin? Now consider how much the city has hyped Austin's visual arts. How many galleries and community art spaces exist in Austin?

